ith moderate cooperation negatives) versus A\u2019s higher technical/leadership strength but more pronounced cooperation and health drawbacks.\n- Remaining uncertainty: How severely B\u2019s grumpiness, pretentious tone, and \u201cnasty remarks\u201d will affect day\u2011to\u2011day crew interaction on ultra\u2011long missions, and whether his relatively weak numeric memory could become safety\u2011critical.\n- What would change my vote: Credible evidence that another candidate (especially A, C, or D) matches B\u2019s reliability, stress handling, and technical competence while demonstrating markedly better cooperative behavior (no hostility, openness to feedback, no health concerns), or evidence that B\u2019s cooperation issues or numeric\u2011memory weakness would critically impair safety on long\u2011distance flights.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}"}
